<h2>Solar Incentives in Charlotte</h2>
<p>Charlotte residents can take advantage of the federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC), which provides a 30% tax credit on the total cost of solar installation through 2032, then drops to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. North Carolina offers additional state-level incentives, including property tax exemptions for solar installations and the state's Renewable Energy Tax Credit program. Duke Energy provides rebates for solar installations through their PowerPair program, offering up to \$9,000 for solar-plus-battery systems, though availability varies and incentives are distributed on a first-come, first-served basis. Charlotte homeowners should also check with Mecklenburg County for any local solar programs or expedited permitting processes.</p>

